      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Week 4 of "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "link",
              "attrs": {
                "href": "https://advisoryhour.substack.com",
                "target": "_blank",
                "rel": "noopener noreferrer nofollow",
                "class": null
              }
            }
          ],
          "text": "Summer into AI 2026"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " hosted by "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "link",
              "attrs": {
                "href": "https://advisoryhour.substack.com",
                "target": "_blank",
                "rel": "noopener noreferrer nofollow",
                "class": null
              }
            }
          ],
          "text": "@advisoryhour"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " — theme: Built on Yesterday."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": null
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The Culper Ring was a one-shot spy dispatch game: decode the message, make the call. Deep Cover turns it into a five-mission arc with a live SVG map of the Culper network, decisions that carry consequences across all five missions, a disinformation mechanic where you write the lie instead of decoding the truth, and Washington's extended-thinking judgment streaming after every mission."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": null
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Worth noting alongside this: "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "link",
              "attrs": {
                "href": "https://advisoryhour.substack.com",
                "target": "_blank",
                "rel": "noopener noreferrer nofollow",
                "class": null
              }
            }
          ],
          "text": "Other week-4 entries"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " extended their demos with more content; Deep Cover added a consequence system and a second AI interaction type (composing disinformation) that changes the game's strategy"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": null,
        "level": 2
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "How the AI works"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bullet_list",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ],
                  "text": "Adaptive mission generation"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " — each of the five missions knows your previous decisions. Claude generates historically authentic cipher dispatches, disinformation scenarios, and moral dilemmas that respond to how you've managed the network so far."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ],
                  "text": "Washington's extended thinking judgment"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " — after each mission, Claude uses 6,000 thinking tokens to evaluate your response against 18th-century intelligence tradecraft. The reasoning panel shows Washington deliberating before his verdict. Each outcome updates the network integrity meter."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ],
                  "text": "Disinformation mechanic"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " — in certain missions you don't decode an incoming dispatch; you write the false one. Claude judges your disinformation for historical plausibility and operational effectiveness."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": null,
        "level": 2
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "How to play"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bullet_list",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Click BEGIN MISSION 1 on the intro screen. The SVG map shows the five Culper Ring agents by location."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "For DECODE missions: read the cipher dispatch, interpret it, and choose the operational response."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "For COMPOSE missions: write a disinformation dispatch that will mislead British forces without burning your agents."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Watch Washington's "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ],
                  "text": "Reasoning"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " panel expand after each mission — [SUCCESS], [PARTIAL], or [FAILURE] shifts the Network Integrity meter. All five missions determine whether the Culper Ring survives."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
